<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376487>
    dc:description "FIGURES 132–137. Orcevia kuloni Prószyński & Deeleman-Reinhold, 2012, male (132, 134–135) and female (133, 136), deposited in MNHN, Paris, labeled as “13193, L. perakensis, Java” (137), without scale bars (© Junxia Zhang). 132–133. Habitus in dorsal view; 134–135. Left palp, in ventro-top (134) and retro-top (135) view; 136. Epigynum in ventral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376487/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376489>
    dc:description "FIGURES 138–141. Orcevia kuloni Prószyński & Deeleman-Reinhold, 2012, male holotype (138–140) and female allotype (141). 138. Left palp in pro-ventral view; 139–140. RTA, in retro-top (139) and retro-ventral (140) view; 141. Vulva in ventral view, modified from Prószyński & Deeleman-Reinhold (2012). Abbreviations: AG, accessory gland; CD, copulatory duct; CO, copulatory opening; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; LPT, lobe like protrusion of tegulum; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermatheca." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376489/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

